{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4ab6944e-5410-45ed-adba-baab1004884a","content":"Here's my assessment — the template is **not quite ready** to publish to NuGet:\n\n### Issues Found in `template.json`\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation and editor support.\n2. **Missing `description`** — Critical for NuGet discoverability. Users won't know what your template does.\n3. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for published templates to group related variants (e.g., `MyCompany.WebApi`).\n\n### Missing Packaging Infrastructure\n\n4. **No `.csproj` or `.nuspec`** — You need a template pack project (a `.csproj` with `<PackageType>Template</PackageType>`) to produce a `.nupkg` for NuGet. Without it, there's no way to `dotnet pack` this into a NuGet package.\n\n### Suggestions\n\n- The `Framework` symbol and `sourceName` look correct.\n- Consider adding `preferNameDirectory: true` for a better `dotnet new` experience.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold the missing packaging project and fix the `template.json`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"52f03c02-19c5-434f-9c8c-84e60c37f37f","outputTokens":277,"requestId":"4803:8D0D7:162EC4:1A5A47:69EABFC7"},"id":"8ff095d6-6a86-4aa5-8ac8-d37c40b65770","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:56:46.913Z","parentId":"76f97f1f-8959-4043-8238-9298f1ec49a1"}
